Full Description: 140Fire is a platform to make online video ads interactive. We have a product called DataRoll, which adds a layer of interactivity on top of an exisiting video ad. Furthermore, using DataRoll increases the likelyhood a consumer will click-through on a video as much as 2x. Advertisers come to us who are looking to achieve a â€œSmart Buyâ€. We not only provide the interactivity, but we also will help advertisers plan out their media spend through our own network of video publishers. What's different about our network? Unlike larger ad networks, we can use DataRoll to effectively see which publishers have an audience that are willing to interact with a specific brand. If consumers aren't engaging, we can quickly adjust on the fly. All of our publishers are DataRoll certified, meaning their users have showed an exceptional willingness to engage with advertising. No other network can say this. We are attracting new advertisers daily, and our revenue is on a rate in the millions of dollars. The venture is backed by Y Combinator, Mark Cuban, Jonnathan Kraft and Skip Paul.

Description: Skyless Game Studios is a serious video game development service that empowers social causes to change the world through gaming.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: Skyless Game Studios leverages the power of video games to support and empower social, educational, and philanthropic causes. We partner with experts on an important cause, then work with them to make a great game with a purpose. Our flagship product is a training game that teaches skills and techniques to corruption investigators. In today’s ever-connected world, engaging an audience can be a real challenge for many organizations. This is especially true for philanthropic, educational, and other social causes. Without a way to capture and hold people’s attention, many great causes fade out before being able to make substantial change. This is why we created Skyless Games: to use fun and engaging video games to help give a voice to the people trying to change the world. Skyless Games’ mission statement is simple: to use video games to empower social causes to create positive change. This single sentence embodies the ideals that drive us everyday at Skyless: pushing for positive change in today’s world and using video games as a medium to do so. Our mission is on our minds with every decision we make: who to work with, how to design a game, what our message is, what’s for lunch (well, maybe not the last one). And it is with this simple mission in mind that we aim to build Skyless into an increasingly valuable resource for social causes around the world.
Founders: Arad Malhotra, Chris Bennett, Oleks Levtchenko

Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Flight Key - a new innovative real time aviation task management, communication, and collaboration platform for your flight ops teams, crews, brokers and passengers to all work in sync. It can be very time consuming sifting through countless text and emails trying to communicate with the Operator or Crew about the status of your active flight. With Flight Key, once a flight is scheduled, you can initiate a new flight by entering all of the flight details and invite as many participants as you want to follow along on the flight. This could include the Operator’s dispatch team, crews, passengers, brokers and any colleagues that you wish to participate on your flight.  You will then assign certain roles and tasks to the individual participants. This essentially eliminates your paper trip sheet, by replacing it with a live interactive solution for tracking all of the flight details in real time from beginning to end on any device. When any tasks or as we call “actions” are completed, then all participants will get a real time stamp notification of that updated status. Flight Key features real time flight communication. - A simplified flight calendar , that you can easily view all of your upcoming flights - See and check off your actions  - Add multiple flights and multiple participants  - Ability to live chat with all flight participants involved at any time. - Real-time movement messages to all participants with the assistance of your cell phone's GPS All leading to better, smarter, more efficient communication and information flow, resulting in time and financial savings, along with higher customer satisfaction.  Invite - Engage - Collaborate – Iterate. flight ops simplified

Description: Photo Sharing for Groups and Events
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: My company is developing a media platform that will deliver the best real-time photo streaming experience for group events, topics and timelines. We call it Fotojelly. By embracing the social components that power the success of Facebook, twitter, and Foursquare and creating mobile apps that seamlessly build albums from multiple cameras, consumers will have richer connected experiences when using their mobile phone cameras and viewing on the web. My name is Chris Ross, and for over 20yrs, I have used technology to empower businesses and most recently to accelerate user adoption of the same. While the photo sharing category has seen explosive growth, it is still a relatively green field, dominated by cookie cutter services and little recouping of investment.  We aim to change that.  Here is how. Through our website, mobile apps and APIs, consumers effortlessly create public or private albums, invite others to contribute, and share those photos in real-time. Our integration with Facebook and Foursquare brings familiarity and efficiencies to tagging, comments, achievement badges, uploading and location awareness.   Businesses and "pro-sumers" too will benefit, subscribing for larger private albums, custom URLs, QR codes and direct feeds to their own systems. In short, we are building a platform that will encompass the best features of the photo sharing services today, and make it easier for the broader consumer market to embrace.

Description: The Center for Responsible Lending (CRL) is a non-partisan research.
Headquarters Regions: Research Triangle, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: The Center for Responsible Lending (CRL) is working to ensure a fair, inclusive financial marketplace that creates opportunities for all responsible borrowers, regardless of their income, because too many hard-working people are deceived by dishonest and harmful lending practices. While the housing crash was devastating to families at all income levels, it was disproportionately destructive to entire communities of low- and moderate-income families and borrowers of color. In fact, it wiped out generations of family wealth in these communities. Many of these families had successful 30-year loans, but they were lured by the promises of deceptive marketing and then financially devastated when they were placed in egregious loan products. CRL is a nonprofit, non-partisan organization that works to protect homeownership and family wealth by fighting predatory lending practices. Their focus is on consumer lending: primarily mortgages, payday loans, credit cards, bank overdrafts and auto loans.

Description: Business Law & Complex Litigation
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: “In a new era of business law, regulations, compliance, management, economics and, let’s face it, survival, one legal challenge can ultimately compromise your organization’s ability to function and in some cases stay in business. Bellatrix PC was formed with one main objective, providing piece of mind to all stakeholders. Principle protection is at the heart of everything we do.” ~ Alicia Dearn, Founder and Managing Attorney Bellatrix PC is a distinctive law firm offering integrated legal solutions to small and medium sized businesses, as well as large enterprises, that seek practical legal advisory to efficiently manage day-to-day operations, employee compliance and, if the time should arise, conflict resolution. Our approach supports the fundamentals of how your organization is structured and operates with a multi-disciplined and experienced team of entrepreneurs and lawyers who will simplistically engage you, your stakeholders, and your teams with dedication towards providing precautions and solutions allowing for your most valued return, peace of mind.   Our diverse, forward thinking, and innovative firm allows us to get down to business to prevent and solve problems – from the simple to the very complex.  We are well versed in business law, employment law, and complex business litigation. Alicia I. Dearn is the Founder and Managing Attorney of Bellatrix, PC, a business and enterprise facing law firm with offices in Saint Louis, Missouri and San Diego, California. Dearn handles civil matters in all areas of business law and employment and labor law.  Acting as an outsourced general counsel for many of her clients, Ms. Dearn takes pride in becoming a part of the internal business team. Her clients come from a diverse portfolio of industries: manufacturing, restaurants, political, retail, software and staffing organizations.   In 2012, Ms. Dearn served as General Counsel to Governor Gary Johnson’s Libertarian campaign for U.S. Presidency and it’s related non-profits and PACs. Most notable was the Libertarian National Committee’s Ballot Access and Litigation Committee, where shesuccessfully defended multiple legal challenges to Gov. Johnson’s placement on ballots. This success earned Dearn a fearless reputation for victoriously going up against some of the nation’s top-ranked election law attorneys in multiple eleventh-hour state electoral proceedings simultaneously.     With a lengthy resume in both federal and state courts, Ms. Dearn’s litigation practice is multi-jurisdictional, sophisticated and full-service handling trials, appeals, complex litigation matters, as well as class actions.

Description: International Biomass Group, Inc. (IBMG) has an extraordinary product and a terrific market opportunity.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: International Biomass Group, Inc. (IBMG) has an extraordinary product and a terrific market opportunity.  In the broadest of strokes, IBMG has a proprietary process that uses beetle kill trees plus a binding agent to create an industrial wood pellet used in coal-fired electrical generation facilities.  The pellets burn at 10,500 British Thermal Units and are used to augment coal on an 80/20 or 70/30 mix.  The pellets burn at a high rate with very little emission. The potential market includes international power plants in countries that are bound by the Kyoto Protocol, as well as domestic plants that cannot meet EPA guidelines.  Since a wood biomass solution is the part of every country’s Kyoto 2020 plan, there is a massive demand for this type of product. The pellets are currently being produced and burned on a smaller scale.  IBMG plans to substantially increase the production scale to produce 360,000 tons or more per year per plant.  IBMG plans to build five plants over the next five – seven years.  IBMG has spent a great deal of time in Asia building relationships, and has a long-term distribution agreement in place to provide product to several South Korea plants. IBMG has commitments for  $6.7 million of $12.2 million project for its first plant.  IBMG is looking for the final $5.5 million through a combination of debt($3 million) and equity($2.5 million).
